CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 15, 1941, pg. 2 reads: " "FROGS" Install New Members - The Frogs, one of Pittsburgh's oldest nad most progressive organizations, installed seven new members last week at a special meeting in Loendi club. Dedicated to social as well as charitable enterprises, plans are being made for various affairs during the 1941-42 season.  The new members include Clyde Page, Cornelius Hones, Max Thompson, Chester Washington, Wendell Smith, Dr. George Little, and William Curtis.  Curtis and Little were not present at the above meeting. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of sixteen FROGS members, including Clyde Page, Cornelius Hones, Max Thompson, Chester Washington, Wendell Smith, gathered behind desk in interior
